{"id":14881846,"mediaExerciseId":"112efebb-f7dc-4368-a1fa-9932618ddf86","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612489,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":789,"solutions":[{"id":6028914,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"**a.** For this, we will use the formula for the fair value of the loan which is given as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Fair value of loan}&=\\dfrac{\\text{Monthly payment} \\times \\left[1-\\left(1+\\dfrac{R}{12}\\right)^{-n}\\right]}{R}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere,\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Monthly payment}&=\\$2,577.21\\\\\nR&=0.07\\\\\nn&=300\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":427,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/91a4cfc14e9b69e9b4242827f3e6603c/0fe565a958c3a99c066a63b9d06ef45f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":213,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/91a4cfc14e9b69e9b4242827f3e6603c/0fe565a958c3a99c066a63b9d06ef45f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting these values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Fair value of loan}&=\\dfrac{\\$2,577.21 \\times \\left(1-\\left(1+\\dfrac{0.07}{12}\\right)^{-300}\\right)}{0.07/12}\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{\\$2,577.21 \\times (1-0.176)}{0.0058}\\\\\n&=\\$366,141.56\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe amount that Ian will be willing to pay for the mortgage is the Fair value of the loan which is $\\$366,141.56$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":403,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/91a4cfc14e9b69e9b4242827f3e6603c/d007a27600473f2b5043c32abf8c970c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":203,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/16/91a4cfc14e9b69e9b4242827f3e6603c/d007a27600473f2b5043c32abf8c970c/lateximg.png"